zile
------------------------------------------
GNU Zile is a text editor development kit, so that you can (relatively)
quickly develop your own ideal text editor without reinventing the wheel for
many of the common algorithms and data-structures needed to do so.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.6-1
  libgee0.8_2-0.20.1-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.87.0-1
  libncursesw10-6.5+20240427-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  autoconf-archive-2024.10.16-1
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cygport-0.37.6-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libgee0.8-devel-0.20.1-1
  libglib2.0-devel-2.87.0-1
  libncurses-devel-6.5+20240427-1
  make-4.4.1-2
  vala-0.56.18-1

Canonical website:
  https://www.gnu.org/software/zile/

Canonical download:
  mirror://gnu/zile/zile-2.6.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack zile-2.6.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./zile-2.6.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/zile-2.6.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/zile-2.6.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(zile)
  /usr/bin/zile.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/zile.README
  /usr/share/doc/zile/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/zile/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/zile/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/zile/FAQ
  /usr/share/doc/zile/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/zile/README
  /usr/share/doc/zile/THANKS
  /usr/share/doc/zile/dotzile.sample
  /usr/share/man/man1/zile.1.gz

